I don't follow basketball.

The rating algorithms that have updated since the tournament started indicate Villanova should be favored (ex: Sagarin, Pomeroy). Villanova has produced the highest offensively efficient game of the entire NCAA season (their S16 win, not the Final Four 40+ point blowout of Oklahoma). UNC has had an easier path to the championship game but is not that improved in its indicators. The -3 point spread favoring UNC seems far too high to me.
Five Thirty Eight currently has the game at a very narrow difference, with 54% favoring UNC. All sports betting markets also favor UNC, with UNC currently at roughly -145 vs +135 for Villanova.
VIL does not have the track record of NC. When the chips are down, the coach makes the difference

Slightly modifying %s based on @GJDrew point about 3-point. Still leaving Villanova high based on great defense.

UNC is the top ranked remaining team, additionally they play Syracuse who is the lowest ranked team remaining which raises the likelihood they advance. Historically speaking, the likelihood that Syracuse advances is non-existent but it's called March Madness for a reason so I gave them a chance. Between Oklahoma and Villanova is a much tougher decision. Recent results seem to favor Oklahoma, I'm not sure Villanova can expect to hold another top-ranked team to such a low shooting percentage beyond the arc, especially with Buddy Hield playing.

My family have a long and strange tradition of supposing that either a team from Florida or a team from North Carolina will prevail at basketball. Nobody knows why. Sooner or later--sooner, I guess, given the deadline--I shall have to look into this.
Since this is just for fun, I think I'm going to switch. I'm impressed by the Villanova no-stars, fundmentals theme, and I think they can upset Oklahoma and the 1 transcendent star team.
